The term '''''oracy''''' was coined by Andrew Wilkinson, a British researcher and educator, in the 1960s. This word is formed by analogy from [[literacy]] and [[numeracy]]. The purpose is to draw attention to the neglect of [[Speech communication|oral skills]] in [[education]].

==References==
*''Oracy Matters: The Development of Talking and Listening in Education'' by Maggie MacLure (Editor), Terry Phillips (Editor), Andrew Wilkinson (Editor) (Open University Press, 1 Jun 1988) {{ISBN|0-335-15855-2}}

